commentary: Mills to Patel, 3 runs another wristy flick, lovely timing, gets it past midwicket, but there is a lot more drama around! Vettori and Guptill chase, Vettori flicks it to Guptill, who sends the throw in towards the striker's end. It is a wide throw, McCullum has to go away and jump high to collect it. And Vettori seems to be telling Saheba that if he thinks there is no inside edge, Sharma is caught dead plumb! Poor umpiring really
